Former Norges Bank Chief Applies For Finance Ministry Position

-- B y   J o s i a n e   K r e m e r
-- 
2011-04-05T12:29:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/former-norges-bank-chief-applies-for-finance-ministry-position.html
     April 5 (Bloomberg) - Former Norwegian Central Bank
Governor  Svein Gjedrem , 61, applied for the position of
secretary general at the  Finance Ministry , the ministry said in
an e-mailed statement today.   Gjedrem, whose second and last term as Norges Bank chairman
ended on Dec. 31, is the only applicant for the position.   The position of secretary general is the permanent
secretary and the chief advisor to the finance minister. Tore
Eriksen, who has held the position since Jan. 1, 1999, will
leave the ministry in June.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
